channel.title: Read this for the sake of your life
channel.description:
Ok everyone i dont think you all understand how fed up i am,
ALL of you people think your so great and wen a new comer asks a question you turn them down and try to make them feel bad. just think how did you get were you are now. you were a noob once too and i dont like the way you all treat these new players and coders.
They are people to and you should listen to them and not yell or be nasty because its just down right being an asshole. :mad: :mad: :mad: :mad:
[glow=red,2,300]Thanks people for listening and if you dont have anything nice to say just dot say anything!!!!! [/glow] :) :) :) ty samcanbam

[quote=“samcanbam, post:1, topic:11894”]Ok everyone i dont think you all understand how fed up i am,

ALL of you people think your so great and wen a new comer asks a question you turn them down and try to make them feel bad.
just think how did you get were you are now. you were a noob once too and i dont like the way you all treat these new players and coders.

They are people to and you should listen to them and not yell or be nasty because its just down right being an asshole. :mad: :mad: :mad: :mad:

[glow=red,2,300]Thanks people for listening and if you dont have anything nice to say just dot say anything!!!
[/glow]
ty samcanbam[/quote]

Ok, I play an old game, Dungeon Siege, because it’s fun(and sometimes easy to mod) and the other day I had an error. I could of asked a few people for help, but I looked at my mod and took me 3 hours to find the error(as you don’t compile your code the only way to test it is go ingame and hope to god it didn’t screw up), want to know what the error was? I put a : at the end of a line insted of ;.

Now, that’s like all the problems that are probally asked here, but insted of spending 3 hours looking at there code/problem they could of found it in 3 minutes DOING 1 GOOGLE SEARCH. Or, ONE FORUM SEARCH. But no, they ask, and when they got help they don’t do it properly and fail.
